## 1. Purpose

A Process Performance Baseline (PPB) establishes the statistical normal operating range of key sub-process metrics, enabling quantitative project management (CMMI L4 QPM). This document is a stub that will be populated once 30+ data points per metric are available.

---

## 2. Candidate Metrics for Baseline

| Metric                           | Sub-process              | Data source                                | Data points available | Target (30+) |
|----------------------------------|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------|----------------------|--------------|
| PR cycle time (open → merge)     | Development              | GitHub API via `maw costs`                 | [N] (as of {{DATE}}) | ≥30          |
| Defect detection rate (UAT)      | QA / Validation          | UAT sign-off records                       | [N]                  | ≥30          |
| Requirements churn rate          | Requirements Mgmt        | SRS revision history counts                | [N]                  | ≥30          |
| Test coverage (unit)             | Development              | CI coverage reports                        | [N]                  | ≥30          |
| Post-release defect density      | Release / Maintenance    | GitHub issues post-release                 | [N]                  | ≥30          |

